{
  "message": "fuzz(verify-ext4-integrity): pin 5 regression seeds for hardening fixes\n\nThe four hardening fixes I committed (b9f00e3) \u2014 inodes_per_group\ndivide-by-zero guard, lazy ino_iter avoiding eager Vec<u32>,\nMAX_GROUPS_VERIFIED cap, and accompanying counter bookkeeping \u2014\neach had at least one libFuzzer-discovered input that previously\npanicked or OOM'd. Promote those 5 artifacts into the corpus as\nnamed regression seeds:\n\n  regression_div_by_zero_inodes_per_group\n    \u2014 original artifact: crash-7a3b65bd... ; was inodes_per_group=0\n      divide-by-zero panic at lib.rs:19019.\n\n  regression_oom_dirty_combined_muts_a\n    \u2014 original artifact: oom-6b657e31... ; mode=Dirty + focused mutate\n      of blocks_count low byte; verifier OOM'd before the cap fix.\n\n  regression_oom_clean_focused_kind3\n    \u2014 original artifact: oom-7ca55d83... ; mode=Clean with kind=3\n      (write_u32_le) hitting interesting offsets via mutate_ext4_image.\n\n  regression_oom_libfuzzer_b / regression_oom_libfuzzer_c\n    \u2014 original artifacts: oom-ade311ab... and oom-e37aa639... ;\n      libFuzzer-mutated descendants of the corpus that uncovered\n      additional unbounded-allocation paths through verify_ext4.\n\nEach runs in <1 s with peak RSS well under 500 MiB post-fix. All\n236 corpus files now replay cleanly (prior 18+5+1=24 named, plus\nlibFuzzer-grown entries). A future regression that re-introduces\nany of the unbounded paths surfaces immediately on `cargo fuzz run\n... -runs=0`.",
